10 "§ 116-74.46. Recipient selection; use of grant funds; duration and conditions of grants;
11 reporting requirements.
12 (a) Selection. – After evaluation of grant applications pursuant to G.S. 116-74.45, the
13 Commission shall notify the Authority of its selection of the recipients of grants for each fiscal
14 year. The Commission shall select up to eight grant recipients to be operating operate a school
15 leader preparation program with grant funds for forgivable scholarship loans in any fiscal
16 year.year and up to two recipients for a grant of up to two hundred fifty thousand dollars
17 ($250,000) per recipient per fiscal year to develop innovative ways of training principals.
18 (b) Use of Funds. Grant Funds for Forgivable Scholarship Loans. – Each eligible entity
19 that receives grant funds for forgivable scholarship loans shall use those funds to carry out the
20 following:
21 …
22 (c) Duration and Conditions of Grants. – The Commission shall also notify the Authority
23 of its decisions on the duration and renewal of grants to eligible entities made in accordance with
24 the following:
25 (1) The duration of grants for forgivable scholarship loans shall be as follows:
26 a. Grants shall be no more than six years and no fewer than two years in
27 duration, unless the Commission finds early termination of a grant is
28 necessary due to noncompliance with grant terms.
29 b. The Commission may renew a grant based on compliance with the
30 grant terms and performance, including allowing the grantee to scale
31 up or replicate the successful program as provided in subdivision (3)
32 of this subsection.
33 (1a) The duration of grants for training development shall be for one year. The
34 Commission may renew a grant for training development, in its discretion, on
35 an annual basis.
36 …
37 (3) In evaluating performance for purposes of grant renewal and making its
38 renewal decisions to provide to the Authority, Authority pursuant to
39 subdivision (1) of this subsection, the Commission shall consider at least the
40 following:
41 …
42 (d) Reporting Requirements for Grant Recipients. – Recipients of grants shall participate
43 in all evaluation activities required by the Commission and submit an annual report to the
44 Commission with any information requested by the Commission. The recipients shall comply
45 with additional report requests made by the Commission. Whenever practicable and within a
46 reasonable amount of time, grant recipients shall also make all materials developed as part of the
47 program and with grant funds publicly available to contribute to the broader sharing of promising
48 practices. Materials shall not include personally identifiable information regarding individuals
49 involved or associated with the program, including, without limitation, applicants, participants,
50 supervisors, evaluators, faculty, and staff, without their prior written consent. The Commission
51 shall work with recipients, local school administrative units, and public schools, as needed, to
