15 PART II. PRINCIPAL FELLOWS PROGRAM MAY USE ADMINISTRATIVE FUNDS
16 FOR STATEWIDE PROGRAMMING
17 SECTION 2. G.S. 116-74.41B reads as rewritten:
18 "§ 116-74.41B. The North Carolina Principal Fellows Trust Fund.
19 …
20 (b) Use of Monies in the Trust Fund. – The monies in the Trust Fund may be used only
21 for the purposes set forth in this subsection, including the award of grants pursuant to
22 G.S. 116-74.44, administrative costs, and costs associated with Program operations in
23 accordance with this Article. The Authority may use up to two percent (2%) of the funds
24 appropriated for the Program or one hundred sixty thousand dollars ($160,000) from the Trust
25 Fund, whichever is greater, each fiscal year for administrative costs, including recovery of funds
26 advanced under the Program, and may allocate to the Commission up to eight hundred thousand
27 dollars ($800,000) from the Trust Fund each fiscal year for the following:
28 (1) The salary and benefits of the director and staff of the Program.
29 (2) The expenses of the Commission to administer the Program.
30 (3) Program monitoring and evaluation.
31 (4) Extracurricular enhancement activities for the Program.
32 (5) Repealed by Session Laws 2019-60, s. 1(y), effective July 1, 2021.
33 (6) Programming on research-based school leadership practices to be shared with
34 eligible entities in order to improve principal preparation throughout the State.
35 (c) Remaining Funds. – If at the end of each fiscal year there are funds remaining in the
36 Trust Fund that are not obligated or otherwise encumbered for another purpose, upon the request
37 of the Commission, the Authority shall allocate the funds to the Commission for any of the
38 purposes identified in subdivisions (3) through (6) of subsection (b) of this section."
39
40 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
41 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
